  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "LOGISTICS MANAGER",
  "description": "<h3>Job Purpose</h3><p>Plan, lead and optimise end-to-end logistics operations to ensure timely, accurate and cost-effective movement and storage of goods, while meeting service, safety, and compliance requirements.</p><h3>Key Responsibilities</h3><ul><li><p>Lead daily logistics operations including inbound/outbound deliveries, warehousing, inventory control, and distribution planning.</p></li><li><p>Develop delivery schedules and route plans to improve on-time performance and reduce transportation cost.</p></li><li><p>Manage warehouse layout, space utilisation, stock accuracy, picking/packing quality, and cycle counts.</p></li><li><p>Coordinate with customers, suppliers, freight forwarders and internal teams to resolve shipment issues and service escalations.</p></li><li><p>Oversee logistics documentation (DO, invoices, POD, shipping documents) and ensure records are properly maintained.</p></li><li><p>Track and report KPIs (on-time delivery, order accuracy, inventory variance, damage rate, cost per shipment).</p></li><li><p>Manage logistics vendors (transporters, couriers, 3PL) including pricing, service levels and performance reviews.</p></li><li><p>Ensure compliance with workplace safety, SOPs, and relevant regulations; implement corrective and preventive actions.</p></li><li><p>Lead, coach and roster the logistics team (drivers, warehouse assistants, coordinators); conduct training and performance reviews.</p></li><li><p>Support continuous improvement projects (process redesign, WMS/TMS improvements, automation, cost saving initiatives).</p></li></ul>",
